{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Most of the LFMs utilized FT and PE in adaptation.a) FT-based adaptation adjusts the parameters of pretrained networks, adapting the LFM to downstream tasks without additional parameters.",
    "A lot of works [16], [63]- [65], [67]- [71], [89], [90] utilized full-parameter FT that directly adjusted all parameters using existing training datasets or human/LLM-generated instructions to improve their performance on target downstream tasks.",
    "For example, BenTsao [63] was fine-tuned on 8K Chinese instruction data from CMeKG-8K [103].",
    "HuatuoGPT [64] was fine-tuned on a mixture of 226k dialogue and instruction data for medical consultation.",
    "PMC-LLaMA [65] was further pre-trained on medical books and papers using a LLaMA [79] model, and then fine-tuned on the constructed instruction data collected from medical conversation [71], medical QA [104], and medical knowledge graph prompting [105]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
